{"title_page": "1981 in baseball", "text_new": "{{See also|1981 Major League Baseball season}}\n{{Year in baseball top\n|  this year = 1981\n}}\n{{Year nav topic5|1981|baseball}}\n\n==Champions==\n\n===Major League Baseball===\n*[[1981 World Series|World Series]]: [[Los Angeles Dodgers]] over [[New York Yankees]] (4-2); [[Ron Cey]], [[Pedro Guerrero (baseball)|Pedro Guerrero]], and [[Steve Yeager]], co-MVPs\n\n{{8TeamBracket | RD1=[[Division Series]] | RD2=[[League Championship Series]] | RD3=[[World Series]] |\n| RD1-seed1= E1 | RD1-team1='''[[New York Yankees]]'''\n| RD1-seed2=E2| RD1-team2=[[Milwaukee Brewers]]\n| RD1-score1=3 | RD1-score2=2\n| RD1-seed3=W1 | RD1-team3='''[[Oakland Athletics]]'''\n| RD1-seed4=W2 | RD1-team4=[[Kansas City Royals]]\n| RD1-score3=3 | RD1-score4=0\n| RD1-seed5=E1 | RD1-team5=[[Philadelphia Phillies]]\n| RD1-seed6=E2 | RD1-team6='''[[Montreal Expos]]'''\n| RD1-score5=2 | RD1-score6=3\n| RD1-seed7=W1| RD1-team7='''[[Los Angeles Dodgers]]'''\n| RD1-seed8=W2| RD1-team8=[[Houston Astros]]\n| RD1-score7=3 | RD1-score8=2\n| RD2-seed1=E | RD2-team1='''[[New York Yankees]]'''\n| RD2-seed2=W | RD2-team2=[[Oakland Athletics]]\n| RD2-score1=3 | RD2-score2=0\n| RD2-seed3=E | RD2-team3=[[Montreal Expos]]\n| RD2-seed4=W | RD2-team4='''[[Los Angeles Dodgers]]'''\n| RD2-score3=2 | RD2-score4=3\n| RD3-seed1=AL | RD3-team1=[[New York Yankees]]\n| RD3-seed2=NL | RD3-team2='''[[Los Angeles Dodgers]]'''\n| RD3-score1=2 | RD3-score2=4\n}}\n\n'''NOTE:''' Due to a [[1981 Major League Baseball strike|strike]] in mid-season, the season was divided into a first half and a second half. The division winner of the first half (denoted East 1, West 1) played the division winner of the second half (denoted East 2, West 2).\n*[[1981 American League Championship Series|American League Championship Series]] MVP: [[Graig Nettles]]\n*[[1981 National League Championship Series|National League Championship Series]] MVP: [[Burt Hooton]]\n*[[1981 Major League Baseball All-Star Game|All-Star Game]], August 9 at [[Cleveland Stadium]]: National League, 5-4; [[Gary Carter]], MVP\n\n===Other champions===\n*[[Minor League Baseball]]\n**AAA\n***[[American Association (20th century)|American Association]]: [[Denver Bears]] (Montreal Expos)\n***[[International League]]: [[Columbus Clippers]] (New York Yankees)\n***[[Pacific Coast League]]: [[Albuquerque Dukes]] (Los Angeles Dodgers)\n***[[Mexican League]]: [[Diablos Rojos del M\u00e9xico]]\n**AA\n***[[Eastern League (baseball)|Eastern League]]: [[Bristol Red Sox]] (Boston Red Sox)\n***[[Southern League (baseball)|Southern League]]: [[Orlando Twins]] (Minnesota Twins)\n***[[Texas League]]: [[Jackson Mets]] (New York Mets)\n**A\n***[[California League]]: [[Rancho Cucamonga Quakes]] (Los Angeles Dodgers)\n***[[Carolina League]]: [[Hagerstown Suns]] (Baltimore Orioles)\n***[[Florida State League]]: [[Daytona Beach Astros]] (Houston Astros)\n***[[Midwest League]]: [[Wausau Timbers]] (Seattle Mariners)\n***[[South Atlantic League]]: [[Greensboro Hornets]] (New York Yankees)\n***[[New York\u2013Penn League]]: [[Oneonta Yankees]] (New York Yankees)\n***[[Northwest League]]: [[Medford Athletics]] (Oakland Athletics)\n**Rookie\n***[[Appalachian League]]: [[Paintsville Yankees]] (New York Yankees)\n***[[Gulf Coast League]]: [[Royals Gold]] (Kansas City Royals)\n***[[Pioneer League (baseball)|Pioneer League]]: [[Butte Copper Kings]] (Milwaukee Brewers)\n'''International'''\n*[[Cuban National Series]]: [[Vegueros de Pinar del R\u00edo]]\n*[[1981 Japan Series|Japan Series]]: [[Yomiuri Giants]] over [[Nippon-Ham Fighters]] (4-2)\n'''Winter Leagues'''\n*[[1981 Caribbean Series]]: [[Leones del Escogido]]\n*[[Dominican Professional Baseball League|Dominican Republic League]]: [[Leones del Escogido]]\n*[[Mexican Pacific League]]: [[Yaquis de Obreg\u00f3n]]\n*[[Puerto Rico Baseball League|Puerto Rican League]]: [[Criollos de Caguas (baseball)|Criollos de Caguas]]\n*[[Venezuelan Professional Baseball League|Venezuelan League]]: [[Leones del Caracas]]\n'''College'''\n*[[1981 College World Series|College World Series]]: [[Arizona State University|Arizona State]]\n'''Youth'''\n*[[1981 Big League World Series|Big League World Series]]: [[Taipei, Taiwan]]\n*[[1981 Junior League World Series|Junior League World Series]]: [[Boardman, Ohio]]\n*[[1981 Little League World Series|Little League World Series]]: Tai-Ping, [[Taichung]], [[Taiwan]]\n*[[1981 Senior League World Series|Senior League World Series]]: [[Georgetown, Delaware]]\n\n==Awards and honors==\n*'''[[Baseball Hall of Fame]]'''\n**[[Rube Foster]]\n**[[Bob Gibson]]\n**[[Johnny Mize]]\n*'''[[MLB Most Valuable Player Award|Most Valuable Player]]'''\n**[[Rollie Fingers]], [[Milwaukee Brewers]], P (AL)\n**[[Mike Schmidt]], [[Philadelphia Phillies]], 3B (NL)\n*'''[[Cy Young Award]]'''\n**Rollie Fingers, Milwaukee Brewers (AL)\n**[[Fernando Valenzuela]], [[Los Angeles Dodgers]] (NL)\n*'''[[MLB Rookie of the Year Award|Rookie of the Year]]'''\n**[[Dave Righetti]], [[New York Yankees]], P (AL)\n**Fernando Valenzuela, Los Angeles Dodgers, P (NL)\n*'''[[Gold Glove Award]]'''\n**[[Mike Squires]] (1B) (AL) \n**[[Frank White (baseball)|Frank White]] (2B) (AL) \n**[[Buddy Bell]] (3B) (AL) \n**[[Alan Trammell]] (SS) (AL) \n**[[Dwight Evans (Baseball)|Dwight Evans]] (OF) (AL) \n**[[Rickey Henderson]] (OF) (AL) \n**[[Dwayne Murphy]] (OF) (AL)\n**[[Jim Sundberg]] (C) (AL) \n**[[Mike Norris (baseball)|Mike Norris]] (P) (AL)\n\n==MLB statistical leaders==\n{| cellpadding=\"1\" style=\"width:auto;font-size: 90%; border: 1px solid gray;\"\n|- align=\"center\" style=\"font-size: larger;\" \n| &nbsp;\n! colspan=2 | [[American League]]\n! colspan=2 | [[National League]]\n|- style=\"background:lightblue;\" \n! Type || Name || Stat || Name || Stat\n|- align=\"center\" style=\"vertical-align: middle;\" style=\"background:lightblue;\"\n|- \n| [[Batting average (baseball)|AVG]] || [[Carney Lansford]] BOS || .336 || [[Bill Madlock]] PIT || .341\n|-\n| [[Home run|HR]] || [[Tony Armas]] OAK<br>[[Dwight Evans (Baseball)|Dwight Evans]] BOS<br>[[Bobby Grich]] CAL<br>[[Eddie Murray]] BAL || 22 || [[Mike Schmidt]] PHI || 31\n|-\n| [[Run batted in|RBI]] || [[Eddie Murray]] BAL || 78 || [[Mike Schmidt]] PHI || 91\n|-\n| [[Win (baseball)|Wins]] || [[Dennis Mart\u00ednez]] BAL<br>[[Steve McCatty]] OAK<br>[[Jack Morris]] DET<br>[[Pete Vuckovich]] MIL || 14 || [[Tom Seaver]] CIN || 14\n|-\n| [[Earned run average|ERA]] || [[Sammy Stewart]] BAL || 2.32 || [[Nolan Ryan]] HOU || 1.69\n|}\n\n==Major league baseball final standings==\n\n===First half of season===\n{{col-begin|width=auto}}\n{{col-break}}\n{| cellpadding=\"1\" style=\"width:auto;font-size: 90%; border: 1px solid gray;\"\n|- align=\"center\" style=\"font-size: larger;\"\n! colspan=6 | [[American League]]\n|- style=\"background:lightblue;\" \n! Rank || Club || Wins || Losses || Win % || GB\n|- align=\"center\" style=\"vertical-align: middle;\" style=\"background:lightblue;\" \n! colspan=6 | East Division\n|-\n|-\n| 1st || [[New York Yankees]] || 34 || 22 || .607 ||&nbsp; &nbsp;--\n|-\n| 2nd || [[Baltimore Orioles]] || 31 || 23 || .574 ||&nbsp; 2.0\n|-\n| 3rd || [[Milwaukee Brewers]] || 31 || 25 || .568 ||&nbsp; 3.0\n|-\n| 4th || [[Detroit Tigers]] || 31 || 26 || .544 ||&nbsp; 3.5\n|-\n| 5th || [[Boston Red Sox]] || 30 || 26 || .536 ||&nbsp; 4.0\n|-\n| 6th || [[Cleveland Indians]] || 26 || 24 || .520 ||&nbsp; 5.0\n|-\n| 7th || [[Toronto Blue Jays]] || 16 || 42 || .276 ||19.0\n|-\n|- align=\"center\" style=\"vertical-align: middle;\" style=\"background:lightblue;\" \n! colspan=6 | West Division\n|-\n| 1st || [[Oakland Athletics]] || 37 || 23 || .617 ||&nbsp; &nbsp;--\n|-\n| 2nd || [[Texas Rangers (baseball)|Texas Rangers]] || 33 || 22 || .600 ||&nbsp; 1.5\n|-\n| 3rd || [[Chicago White Sox]] || 31 || 22 || .585 ||&nbsp; 2.5\n|-\n| 4th || [[California Angels]] || 31 || 29 || .517 ||&nbsp; 6.0\n|-\n| 5th || [[Kansas City Royals]] || 20 || 30 || .400 ||12.0\n|-\n| 6th || [[Seatt